
                        Section 2 - Notes
                        VOLUME Instruction
                          Sharing Volumes

1.  Show file contents in host data directory.

    $ cat data/file.txt
    This is line 1.
    This is line 2.

2.  Run detached volc1 container with -v option. 
    Map host data in current dir to /app in volc1 container.

    $ docker run -d --name volc1 -v "$(pwd)"/data:/app \
    alpine tail -f /dev/null

3.  Show file.txt in host data directory mapped to 
    /app/file.txt in volc1 container.

    $ docker exec volc1 cat /app/file.txt
    This is line 1.
    This is line 2. 

4.  Run detached volc2 container with --volumes-from option.
    Share volume with volc1.

    $ docker run -d --name volc2 --volumes-from volc1 \
    alpine tail -f /dev/null

5.  Show file.txt in host data directory shared 
    between volc1 and volc2 containers.

    $ docker exec volc2 cat /app/file.txt
    This is line 1.
    This is line 2. 

6.  Delete second line in data/file.txt on host.

    $ cat data/file.txt
    This is line 1.

7.  Verify that shared files are seen by both containers.

    $ docker exec volc1 cat /app/file.txt
    This is line 1.

    $ docker exec volc2 cat /app/file.txt
    This is line 1.
